WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.600
A replay batch can contain five rows but behave like fewer samples when one importance ratio dominates.

00:05.600 --> 00:11.700
Normalized effective sample size squares the ratio sum, then divides by sample count times the sum of squared ratios.

00:11.700 --> 00:18.000
FeynRL uses ESS as a batch-reliability signal. Low ESS tightens score-function capping and adds behavioral KL regularization.

00:18.000 --> 00:22.900
ESS is not reward or policy quality. The five-row calculation is only an explanatory toy.

00:22.900 --> 00:30.267
The authors report matching or exceeding tuned baselines without new objective hyperparameters. A dominant ratio lowers effective sample count.
